    management: ["Initiate high-quality CPR immediately (100–120 compressions/min, 2-inch depth)", "Epinephrine 1 mg IV/IO every 3–5 minutes", "Asystole is NOT a shockable rhythm—do not defibrillate", "PEA is NOT a shockable rhythm—do not defibrillate", "Search for and treat reversible causes (H's and T's)", "Advanced airway management with continuous waveform capnography", "Consider sodium bicarbonate for known hyperkalemia or severe acidosis"],
    nursingActions: ["Confirm pulselessness by checking carotid pulse for 5–10 seconds", "Activate code team and initiate CPR immediately", "Ensure high-quality chest compressions with minimal interruptions (<10 sec)", "Prepare and administer epinephrine 1 mg IV every 3–5 minutes", "Monitor end-tidal CO2 (ETCO2): target >10 mmHg during CPR", "Assist with identifying and treating reversible causes", "Document code events, interventions, and times accurately"],
