    assessmentFindings: ["Hypothyroidism: fatigue, weight gain, cold intolerance, constipation, bradycardia", "Hyperthyroidism: weight loss, heat intolerance, tachycardia, exophthalmos, tremor", "Hyperglycemia: polyuria, polydipsia, polyphagia, blurred vision", "Hypoglycemia: tremors, diaphoresis, confusion, tachycardia", "Cushing syndrome: moon face, central obesity, striae, hyperglycemia", "Addison disease: hyperpigmentation, hypotension, fatigue, salt craving"],
